Samsung has launched a new Galaxy A series smartphone, the Galaxy A70. The device features a 6.7-inch Infinity-U display and a 4,500mAh battery, impressive specifications for a non-flagship device. The phone also packs up to 8GB of RAM, 128GB of storage with microSD support (512GB), a 32MP front-facing camera, and Android 9.0. “Built with Samsung’s latest innovations and upgraded essential features, the Galaxy A70 showcases a stylish design, large infinity display, enhanced triple camera, powerful battery, and seamless connectivity,” said Samsung. “Available in four distinctive colours – Coral, Blue, Black, and White – the Galaxy A70 features a stylish prism effect that reveals stunning gradient colours,” it added. No pricing information was revealed at the time of writing. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300658" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Image.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Image.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Image-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Image-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300656" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Back.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Back.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Back-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/A70-Back-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300660" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Galaxy-A70-Header.jpg" alt="" w